cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on unsupervised lexical semantic change detection (LSCD) in German. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses various NLP architectures and evaluation frameworks, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of word embeddings, which could be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of different systems, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
